  <para>
    <classname>RemoveNodes</classname> is a <xref
    linkend="RegisteredClass-BoundaryModifier"/>, used as the
    <varname>modifier</varname> argument of the <xref
    linkend="MenuItem-OOF.Skeleton.Boundary.Modify"/> command when
    editing &skel; <link
    linkend="Section-Concepts-Skeleton-Boundary">boundaries</link>.
    It removes the given set of &nodes; from the <link
    linkend='Section-Concepts-Skeleton-Boundary-Point'>point
    boundary</link> specified in the <varname>boundary</varname>
    argument of the <command>Modify</command> command.  The &nodes;
    are specified by the <varname>group</varname> parameter, which
    must be either the name of a &node; group or the special <xref
    linkend="Object-Placeholder"/> object,
    <userinput>selection</userinput>.
  </para>
  <para>
    If any of the &nodes; to be removed are not part of the
    boundary, <classname>AddNodes</classname> will silently ignore
    them.
  </para>

